content:
Configure Model Quality Notifications

Models drift when characteristics in real-world data diverge from training data used to build them. Einstein can send alert notifications if model performance falls below configured thresholds.

To configure performance alerts:

View a Prediction Definition that uses automated writeback fields.
Click Set Up next to Model Quality Notifications.
Enable any of the following alert conditions:
  - Prediction accuracy decreases
  - Too many missing values
  - Too many out-of-bounds values
  - Has disparate impact

Configure settings for enabled alert conditions, including:

  - Alert threshold (e.g., percentage decrease in true positive rate)
  - Notify recipients only the first time this condition is reached
  - Frequency of evaluation (Weekly or Monthly)

Specify email addresses of notification recipients.

Note: When deploying a model version, Einstein resets performance statistics and clears history for previous versions.
title: Configuring Model Quality Notifications in Salesforce Einstein
